article.headline: Valparaiso 80, W. Illinois 56
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. (AP) -- Samuel Haanpaa came off the bench to score 18 points and grab six rebounds and lead Valparaiso to an 80-56 victory over Western Illinois Thursday night. Shawn Huff had 14 points and Brandon McPherson added 13 points for the Crusaders (14-13, 7-5 Mid-Continent Conference). The Crusaders led 31-26 at halftime and a 3-pointer by Haanpaa with 6:38 left in the game pushed the Valparaiso lead to 28 points. Haanpaa scored 15 of his points in Valparaiso's 49-point second half as the Crusaders shot 18-of-26 (69 percent) from the floor after halftime. Xavier Price led the Leathernecks (6-21, 2-10) with 13 points on 6-of-12 shooting. Western Illinois was called for 24 fouls which Valparaiso turned into 19 points at the free-throw line.
